                <head>175. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>On April 15, 1967, <persName corresp="#p_BFM1">Francis Bator</persName>,
                    President’s Deputy Special Assistant for National Security Affairs, testified
                    before the President’s Task Force on Government Organization. During a
                    presentation that focused on the larger issue of managing interdepartmental
                    foreign pol icy-making, <pb facs="0429" n="395" xml:id="pg_395"/> Bator also
                    commented on the specific foreign policy role of the White House staff. For text
                    of his notes on that part of his presentation, see <ref target="#d118">Document
                        118</ref>, Part III, Role of the White House Staff.</p>
            </div>
